long_desc.thetext:
Hi,
We used qooxdoo-0.8.2-sdk to develop an application. In a page we used qx.ui.embed.Html( ) to have some html content. In this version of qooxdoo, the scrollbar (appears to be native) was working fine.
To resolve some other issue of IE 8, we took the Revision 20145 from qooxdoo SVN . In this version the embed.Html's scroll bar does not respond to mousewheel event, but mouse drag and Key up/down work.
Attached a sample application for reproducing the bug. The page contains a splitpane, the second split contains some tabs. The first tab contains some HTML content with overflows set to 'auto'. Here you can find that the scrollbar does not respond to mousewheel events.
Thanks & Regards, Narasimha

Created attachment 602 Sample application for reproducing the bug
Please let me know if you are not able to reproduce the bug.

to Fabian.
@Narasimha: are all browsers affected?
Yes, behavior is same across Mozilla and IE (on windows).
Closed all bugs already shipped with a release.
